  "text": "One class of agents that is currently used to target EGFR in the treatment of metastatic CRC (mCRC) is the monoclonal antibodies (MoAbs), which compete with endogenous ligands, including EGF and TGF-α to block ligand-dependant activation of EGFR, and induce receptor internalization and consequent downregulation [CITATION_1] . This paper reviews the safety profile of the anti-EGFR MoAbs cetuximab and panitumumab in the treatment of mCRC.",
